title: What data can be backed up on my phone?
answer:
You can back up your contacts, messages, calendar, call log, system settings, alarms,   

bookmarks, notes, HiSpace, weather clock, music playlists, email accounts, and applications.   

Before restoring your phone to its factory settings, you can back up your contacts, messages,   

calendar, call log, system settings, alarms, bookmarks, notes, HiSpace, weather clock, music   

playlists, and email accounts.
